# Prompt Factory

Patterns for writing Claude Code prompts for {{PROJECT_NAME}}. A prompt is a **contract**, not a wish: it names the paths, the single change, what may and may not be edited, and how the result will be checked. A vague prompt produces vague work; the cost of precision here is repaid many times over in the result.

## 1. Pre-Prompt Checklist

1. Re-read `docs/entrypoint.md` section 0 and put the path-variable header (section 2) at the top of the prompt.
2. Name the task mode (`docs/operations/operation-modes.md`) and the single {{EXPERIMENT_UNIT_LABEL}} or change it touches. One prompt, one intent.
3. State the edit scope: which files may change, which are read-only.
4. Prefer subtracting or simplifying before adding.
5. Check the relevant operational constraints (`docs/operations/rules/operational-constraints.md`).
6. Verify every path, code token, and number against current files with rg / view — never from memory.
7. Give a concrete verification step the executor can run and you can check.

